{"id":1700433,"retrievedAt":"2026-05-23T12:20:14.507Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":99,"name":"Documentary"}],"homepage":"https://kyivindependent.com/war-crimes/no-god-but-theirs/","id":1700433,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["UA"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"Не буде Бога, крім їхнього","overview":"Melitopol, a city in Ukraine's southern Zaporizhzhia Oblast, has traditionally been a hub of religious and cultural diversity. Numerous Christian churches operated there, not only coexisting but also effectively collaborating with one another. Among them, Protestant churches were some of the most active and influential.  Immediately following the start of Russia's occupation of Melitopol and the wider region in 2022, local Christians faced repression. Clergy were subjected to searches and interrogations by Russian forces. Eventually, several churches were banned and stripped of all property, including their buildings. Priests were either officially deported or forced to flee under threat, with Russian propaganda often accusing them of stockpiling weapons and ammunition. Believers were forced to go underground.","popularity":0.0071,"poster_path":"/4xuQ2OgAgPbjCz11ojP5qcEIlQQ.jpg","production_companies":[{"id":251670,"logo_path":"/hLn81UTLgRYAkkftIza00lg1OOh.png","name":"The Kyiv Independent","origin_country":"UA"}],"production_countries":[],"release_date":"2025-05-29","revenue":0,"runtime":64,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[],"status":"Released","tagline":"Russia's crackdown on Ukrainian Christians, unmasked","title":"No God But Theirs","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[],"crew":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":5465333,"known_for_department":"Writing","name":"Danylo Mokryk","original_name":"Данило Мокрик","popularity":0.0168,"profile_path":"/aBzAIg5nHAyx6kmpCLXnjWKyUEY.jpg","credit_id":"6a106f63f815cfc9d7825c82","de